04, \"to\": 4116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Green and blue are also desirable choices as these are less prone to wearing and fading.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Green\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4124}, {\"ngram\": \"blue\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4133}, {\"ngram\": \"desirable choices\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most running tracks are made from a multilayered system composed of rubber andplastic.\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4295, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most running tracks\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4228}, {\"ngram\": \"a multilayered system\", \"from\": 4243, \"to\": 4264}, {\"ngram\": \"rubber andplastic\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historically, they were constructed from rubber and asphalt, while some incorporated sand or even hay.\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rubber\", \"from\": 4338, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"asphalt\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1960s saw the arrival of polyurethane surfaces.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4452, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 1960s\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4410}, {\"ngram\": \"the arrival\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4426}, {\"ngram\": \"polyurethane surfaces\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4451}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mexico City Olympics in 1968 marked the first time a synthetic system was used at an international track-and-field event.\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4458, \"end\": 4469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999990423021, \"rank\": 9.577427837578867e-10, \"text\": \"Mexico City\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 4493, \"to\": 